  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Primary School Building Infrastructure</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Displaced children</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Thiotte is located in a high-priority area for education. Approximately 30,000 displaced Haitians settled in the Thiotte area following the earthquake. The community&#x2019;s five primary schools, which were housed in chapels, saw enrollment increase 25 to 30%. The chapels were insufficient for the dramatically increased demand - lacking potable water and sanitary facilities. JRS decided to create a healthy and conducive learning environment for students. Partnering with Sacre Coeur Parish, the project used local labor and construction materials to build five six-room schools. Community involvement has given the people ownership of the schools and their children&#x2019;s future success. Most importantly, 640 students are receiving a proper education. JRS is funding the teacher salaries for the next school year.</narrative>
  </description>
